{
  "texts": [
    "Remark 3.6.",
    "There is a different way of thinking about a Stokes local system, namely as a \"local system on a fission surface\".",
    "Let us briefly reflect on this notion here (as already alluded to in [Boa09, §4], see also [Boa14, §3.1] and the picture on the title page of [Boa21]).",
    "The principal idea is to split the above halo into several pieces given by the active exponents.",
    "More precisely, we can construct a fission surface Σ(Θ) as follows: Let Σ = P 1 be the Riemann sphere, and fix an irregular class Θ at ∞."
  ]
}